name: acts_as_licensed
description: Acts As Licensed is a plugin which provides a basic content licensing system to community centred Ruby On Rails applications. The plugin includes a set of Creative Commons New Zealand and Australian licenses, which can be imported (excluding the No Derivative Works variant).

name: acts_as_zoom
description: A plugin to allow searching and populating of ZOOM Z39.50 servers.

name: better_send_file
description: A project to provide a more efficient send_file method for Ruby on Rails’ ActionController by sending files directly via reverse proxy servers. Currently only supports Nginx.

name: convert_attachment_to
description: A plugin that will take the value of an uploaded file, convert it to either text or HTML, and insert it into specified attribute. Only works with PDF, MS Word, HTML, and plain text documents currently.

name: validates_as_sanitized_html
description: If you have a model that has an attribute that is user submitted HTML, such as comment, etc. this is a useful plugin for warning the user that they have submitted insecure HTML code, such as form elements, or javascript.

name: tiny_mce
description: A Ruby on Rails plugin (pre-Rails 3.1) that allows easy implementation of the TinyMCE editor into your applications.

name: kete
description: Kete was developed by Horowhenua Library Trust and Katipo Communications Ltd. to build a digital library of Horowhenua material.

name: capistrano-configuration
description: Write application configuration files on deployment with Ruby

name: feedzirra
description: A feed fetching and parsing library that treats the internet like Godzilla treats Japan: it dominates and eats all.

name: external_search_sources
description: Display results from external search sources

name: translate
description: A Ruby on Rails plugin with a web interface for translating I18n texts

name: mongo_translatable
description: Rails specific I18n model localization, ala Globalize2, backed by MongoDB rather than an RDBMS. May include UI elements, too.

name: kete_translatable_content
description: An add-on to the Kete application to provide content translations. Relies on the mongo_translatable gem.

name: tiny_mce_plugin_example
description: An example gem using the tiny_mce gems plugin support

name: http_url_validation_improved
description: A variant of HTTP URL Validation is a Rails plugin that allows you to validate a URL  entered in a form. It validates if the URL exists by hitting it with a HEAD  request (and the improvements include retrying with other variants until it fails decisively).

name: oembed_provider
description: A Rails engine to answer oEmbed requests for application media asset models. I.e. this gem allows your application to act as an oEmbed Provider.

name: trollied
description: A slightly different take on a Rails shopping cart engine.

name: media_selector
description: A jQuery and Sammy.js based mini-application for choosing from a list of providers' media assets (images, audio, video, etc.). Used OpenSearch and oEmbed.

name: Google-Maps-for-Rails
description: Enables easy display of items (taken from a Rails 3 model) with Google Map, OpenLayers, Bing or Mapquest. Geocoding + Directions included. Provides much options: markers customization, infowindows, auto-adjusted zoom, polylines, polygons, circles etc... See wiki  for full description and examples.

name: image_selector_tinymce_plugin
description: Using media_selector as the basis of a tinymce plugin for choosing from an existing image from a specified provider or uploading a new image to the provider and returning HTML for image to TinyMCE editor instance.

name: tiny_mce_plugin_imageselector
description: A wrapper gem for installing https://github.com/kete/image_selector_tinymce_plugin so that the tinymce gem can use it.

name: kete_gets_trollied
description: A Kete add-on that uses the Trollied gem to deliver ordering of items from Kete.

name: homebrew
description: The missing package manager for OS X.

name: kete_trackable_items
description: NO LONGER MAINTAINED! Do not use! A Rails engine gem that works in conjunction with kete_gets_trollied to track where an item (with a corresponding physical archive) is physically located.

name: kete_browserid
description: An add-on for Kete that replaces normal login and registration with a browserid based login.

name: rails-authorization-plugin
description: This plugin provides a flexible way to add authorization to Rails.

name: attachment_fu
description: Treat an ActiveRecord model as a file attachment, storing its patch, size, content type, etc.
